#. Tag: title
#: basics.docbook:156
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Entering Data"
msgstr "Ibyatanzwe biva Inyuma"

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:157
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Entering data into a cell can be as simple as selecting the cell, typing "
"your data, then pressing &Enter; or moving the selection to another cell "
"with one of the <keysym>arrow</keysym> keys. Depending on how you enter the "
"data, &sheets; will interpret it as a number, date, time or text:"
msgstr ""
"Ibyatanzwe A Akazu Nka Byoroheje Nka i Akazu , Kwandika :$1 Ibyatanzwe , "
"Hanyuma <keycap> </keycap> Cyangwa Kwimura i Ihitamo Kuri Akazu Na: Rimwe "
"Bya i <keysym> Akambi </keysym> Utubuto . ku Injiza i Ibyatanzwe , &kspread; "
"Nka A Umubare , Itariki: , Igihe Cyangwa Umwandiko : "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:162
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Numbers are entered in the obvious way; <userinput>123</userinput>, "
"<userinput> -123</userinput>, <userinput>456.7</userinput> or in scientific "
"notation <userinput>-1.2E-5</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"in i ; <userinput> </userinput> , <userinput> - </userinput> , <userinput> . "
"7 </userinput> Cyangwa in Cya gihanga <userinput> - 1 . - 5 </userinput> . "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:167
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dates should be entered in your <quote>System</quote> format, as defined in "
"the &systemsettings; in <menuchoice><guimenu>Locale</guimenu> <guisubmenu> "
"Country/Region &amp; Language</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Date &amp; Time</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> tab. If, for example, you are using the DD/MM/"
"YYYY form you should enter <userinput>30/03/2012</userinput> for 30th March "
"2012. Leading zeroes can be omitted from the day and month fields and only "
"the last one or two digits of the year need to be entered if the date is in "
"the current century, for example <userinput>9/1/9</userinput> for 9th "
"January 2009."
msgstr ""
"in <quote> </quote> Imiterere , Nka in i Ibikubiyemo <menuchoice> "
"<guisubmenu> </guisubmenu> <guisubmenu> </guisubmenu> <guimenuitem> &amp; </"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> Ikiganiro Agasanduku . , ya:  Urugero: , ikoresha "
"i /MM /Ifishi %S: Injiza <userinput> //</userinput> ya:  . Kuva: i &Umunsi "
"na ukwezi: Amashami: na i Iheruka Rimwe Cyangwa Kabiri Bya i umwaka: Kuri "
"NIBA i Itariki: ni in i KIGEZWEHO , ya:  Urugero: <userinput> 9 /1 /2 </"
"userinput> ya:  . "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:177
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Times should also be entered using the <quote>System</quote> format. For "
"example if you are using a 12 hour clock then enter times in HH:MIN am|pm or "
"HH:MIN:SS am|pm format such as <userinput>9:42 am</userinput> or <userinput> "
"10:30:52 pm</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"ikoresha i <quote> </quote> Imiterere . Urugero: NIBA ikoresha A 12 ISAHA "
"Isaha Hanyuma Injiza Times in : am | pm Cyangwa : : am | pm Imiterere Nka "
"<userinput> 9 : am </userinput> Cyangwa <userinput> 10 : : pm </userinput> . "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:183
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&sheets; defines any input data as <quote>text</quote> if it cannot "
"recognize the data as being a number, date or time."
msgstr ""
"&kspread; Icyo ari cyo cyose Iyinjiza Ibyatanzwe Nka <quote> Umwandiko </"
"quote> NIBA i Ibyatanzwe Nka A Umubare , Itariki: Cyangwa Igihe . "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:188
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, &sheets; right justifies numbers, dates and times within a cell "
"and left justifies anything else. This can be a useful guide to whether you "
"have entered a date or time in the correct format. But remember that how "
"items are displayed can be changed by altering the <link linkend=\"formatdata"
"\">cell format</link>."
msgstr ""
"Mburabuzi , &kspread; Iburyo: Imibare , Amatariki na Times muri A Akazu na "
"Ibumoso: Ikindi . A Kuri A Itariki: Cyangwa Igihe in i Imiterere . Kwibuka "
"Ibigize Byahinduwe ku i <link linkend=\"formatdata\"> Akazu Imiterere </"
"link> . "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:194
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main text entry box in the <guilabel>Cell Editor</guilabel> tool options "
"provides an easy way of editing the contents of a selected cell. Press "
"&Enter; or <mousebutton>left</mousebutton> click on the green tick mark when "
"you are happy with what you have entered, or click on the red cross to "
"cancel your edits."
msgstr ""
"Umwandiko Icyinjijwe Agasanduku in i Umwanyabikoresho Bya Guhindura i "
"Ibigize Bya A Byahiswemo Akazu . <keycap> </keycap> Cyangwa <mousebutton> "
"Ibumoso: </mousebutton> Kanda ku i Icyatsi Ikimenyetso Ryari: Na: , Cyangwa "
"Kanda ku i Umutuku Kwambukiranya Kuri Kureka . "

#. Tag: title
#: basics.docbook:202
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Generic Cell Format"
msgstr "Imiterere y'Umwanya"

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:203
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&sheets; uses the <quote>Generic</quote> cell format as default. As long as "
"this format is used, &sheets; autodetects the actual data type depending on "
"the current cell data. For example if you enter some text into a cell and "
"later enter a number into the same cell, &sheets; automatically interprets "
"the new data as a number. If you want to define the type of data yourself, "
"you can explicitly set it in the <link linkend=\"formatdata\">cell format</"
"link>. You can change the format back to <quote>Generic</quote> at any time."
msgstr ""
"&kspread; i <quote> </quote> Akazu Imiterere Nka Mburabuzi . Birebire Nka "
"iyi Imiterere ni Byakoreshejwe , &kspread; i Ibyatanzwe Ubwoko: ku i "
"KIGEZWEHO Akazu Ibyatanzwe . Urugero: NIBA Injiza Umwandiko A Akazu na Nyuma "
"Injiza A Umubare i Akazu , &kspread; mu buryo bwikora: i Gishya Ibyatanzwe "
"Nka A Umubare . Kuri Kugaragaza... i Ubwoko: Bya Ibyatanzwe , Gushyiraho in "
"i <link linkend=\"formatdata\"> Akazu Imiterere </link> . Guhindura... i "
"Imiterere Inyuma Kuri <quote> </quote> Ku Icyo ari cyo cyose Igihe . "

#. Tag: title
#: basics.docbook:217
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Copy, Cut and Paste"
msgstr ", na "

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:219
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At first glance, &sheets;'s <guimenuitem>Cut</guimenuitem>, "
